Introduction

Kim Jun Myeon, better known by his stage name Suho (meaning "guardian" in Korean), is a South Korean singer and actor under SM Entertainment. He is the leader and lead vocalist of the boy group EXO and its sub-unit EXO-K.

Suho trained for about 7 years before finally debuting in 2012 as the Leader and Guardian of EXO. Suho also worked as an actor in the movie "One Way Trip" and "Student A." Suho has also starred in a lead role in the drama "The Universe's Star" and "Rich Man."

Suho debuted as a solo artist on March 30, 2020, with the mini-album "Self-Portrait."

He enlisted in the military as a public service officer on May 14, 2020. He completed his service on February 13, 2022.
